All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbstractTaskList
Class represents an abstract task list, methods used to manipulate a task list information Contains three fields a string for taskListName, an int for completedCount, and a swap list of tasks TaskList methods provide functionality for managing tasks in an active list.
ActiveTaskList
Class represents an active task list, extending AbstractTaskList for tasks with an active boolean value set to true.
ISortedList<E extends Comparable<E>>
Interface for a list that keeps objects in sorted order as defined by the Comparable interface.
ISwapList<E>
Interface for a list that changes the position of elements through swap operations.
Notebook
The Notebook Class controls the creation of task lists and tasks.
NotebookReader
The NotebookReader class handles the input side of the IO package in which it contains three methods, readNotebookFile, proccess TaskList, and process Task which will parse through a file for tasks.
NotebookWriter
The NotebookWriter class handles the output side of the IO package in which it contains one method, writeNotebookFile which will use a print stream to output a list of tasklists to output file.
SortedList<E extends Comparable<E>>
Class for a sorted list using linked nodes Contains methods to add, remove, a task list, and methods to check if the element is in the list and to get that specific list.
SwapList<E>
Class for a custom array based list called SwapList Contains methods to add, remove, or prioritize tasks by moving up/down the list SwapList can contain duplicates
Task
The class is used to manipulate task information with standard getters/setters for the fields and is used to create task lists.
TaskList
Represents a task list, extending AbstractTaskList and implementing the Comparable interface.
WolfTasksGUI
Container for the WolfTasks project that provides the user the ability to interact with notebooks, task lists, and tasks.
